06.Sept.1987 in Finland

  This is my first version of RistiNolla game. RistiNolla is name of this
game in Finnish and means something like CrossZero. This game is also called
as Go-Moku (what a name).
  Current version (1.0) is compiled with Lattice 3.3. Despite Lattice's lazy
code this program makes its decisions immediately and is only 24k long. That
is pretty short for graphics Artifical Intelligence -program made in C. This
version should be fully debugged in order to keep your interest in playing
instead of waiting for Guru's next appearance.
  This program is shareware and anyone finding this program useful will be
expected (and hoped) to send a nice postcard about his/her country to me.
Voluntary $10 will be received warmly. If you send me ten bucks I will send
you the new version (when it is ready) plus a disk. Cheap is it?

F.U.S.E.  (Finland Amiga Users)
Mika Pihlajamäki
