  For anybody wanting to know how this program works and why it is so damned
good I can tell that it is my own algorithm and I haven't even looked at
anyone else's code that plays Go-Moku or Tic-Tac-Toe because I thought it
could only mess up my own strategy.
  I am going to start studying PROLOG at the local University of Technology
and construct this algorithm in PROLOG in the near future. Before that I will
make this C version to think ahead in order to make it perfect Master. I have
already started to add new features and logic to it and it will be complete
before winter -87.
  If you happen to find out anything useful for me, please let me know and I
can send you free copy of the new version.
Thank you for reading this introduction and thank you Mr. Fish for
